It did not happen due to personalities, but because of the sense of the German nation. The basic strategy of Walter Ulbricht and the GDR government distinguishes it from the politics of Ceauşescu and the Romanian people in 1989. Gorbachev spoke for months in the press, calling for Romanian revolutionaries to formulate well-reasoned demands. The last Romanian words uttered by Iosif Stalin were: They will never eat hunger! Oaşă, ţăranilor! When there is a choice between Stalin and Gorbachev, the Romanians chose better!

Every Romanian adult lives marginally better than he did 10 years ago. The most frequent joke is: The year 2000 is a very interesting year, and the main thing about it is that you move the first digit to the right. The ten years of transition consisted of getting used to the idea, in Russia, that people have to pay for school, electricity, phone, etc. Erecting the fence around the Kremlin is not a symptom of danger for Russian leaders, but rather a symptom of the brand of worldwide leadership that Putin has inherited.
